    {
      "id": "3e68f10d54a23ecc8858696a504af23c4afdc527",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-04-24 15:00:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nComment about LDLM then inode lock is correct, but I don't follow the comment about lli_lsm_sem providing mutual exclusion.\n\nIn my copy of master, lli_lsm_sem is only taken for write (which would be required for mutual exclusion, all the other users are using it for read) in:\nll_update_lsm_md, and it is released in that function.\n\nHow does that provide mutual exclusion for migrates?\n\nAlso, are we sure that inode lock here is only used for mutual exclusion between migrates?\n\nThe patch which I believe added it says this:\n\"    LU-4712 llite: lock the inode to be migrated\n\n    Because the inode and its connected dentries will be cleared\n    out of the cache after migration, the inode needs to be locked\n    during the migration.\"\n\nWhich is not about mutual exclusion.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
